        <scopecontent id="aspace_683c8e1ed43235914f7869587f80aef3">
          <head>Scope and Contents</head>
          <p>This volume contains the records of a debate which followed an incident where two
            choirs, one hired by the church and a second hired by the town, both claimed the right
            to lead the singing. The result was that, at mass, each choir sang the hymn to different
            tunes at the same time. Debate continued for three years following the incident.</p>
        </scopecontent>
